                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/poli-325d1" class="program-course-title">
              POLI 325D1 Government and Politics: United States (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-33851" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Political Science (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Political Science              : A survey of the American political system, with emphasis on the constitutional and philosophical setting, the institutions and their interactions, the political process, public policy issues, and political change.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Harold M Waller (Fall)                  </p>

    
